---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { FORUM_URL, withBase } from '../../lib/site';
---

<Base title="Tutorial" description="From first start to your personal dashboard: a friendly step-by-step tour through Cardo.">
  <h1>Your first dashboard, step by step</h1>
  <p class="muted">
    Ten minutes from a blank canvas to a board that fits your life. No prior knowledge needed –
    and nothing you do here leaves your device.
  </p>

  <section class="card step">
    <h2>1 · First start: say hi</h2>
    <p>
      When Cardo opens for the first time it asks for your <strong>name</strong> (everything else
      is optional). This is a purely local profile – it exists so Cardo can greet you, not so
      anyone can reach you. There is no account and no sign-up.
    </p>
    <p>
      Right after that, the built-in <strong>interactive tour</strong> starts and highlights the
      real buttons on screen. You can skip it at any point and restart it later under
      <em>Settings → Help → Restart tour</em>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card step">
    <h2>2 · Edit mode: shape your board</h2>
    <p>
      Press <kbd>Cmd/Ctrl + E</kbd> (or the button in the top bar) to unlock the canvas. Now you
      can <strong>drag widgets around, resize them</strong> at the edges, and remove them with
      the ✕ in their toolbar. Press <kbd>Cmd/Ctrl + E</kbd> again to lock everything in place.
    </p>
    <p>
      In edit mode a <strong>“+ Add widget”</strong> button appears – it lists every active tool.
      Add a To-Do list and a clock to start; you can always rearrange later.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card step">
    <h2>3 · Pages: one board per life area</h2>
    <p>
      The tabs in the top bar are <strong>dashboard pages</strong> – for example “Work”,
      “Private”, “Focus”. In edit mode, create a new page with <em>+</em>, rename one with a
      double-click, and delete it with the ✕ on the active tab.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card step">
    <h2>4 · The tool market</h2>
    <p>
      Open <strong>⊞ Tools</strong> in the top bar. Every tool ships with Cardo and runs locally –
      “activating” just switches it on. The <strong>privacy traffic light</strong> shows for each
      tool what it does with your data: <span style="color:var(--success)">green</span> = fully
      local, <span style="color:var(--warning)">yellow</span> = contacts the internet, always with
      a plain-language explanation of what exactly would be sent.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card step">
    <h2>5 · The command palette: everything, one keystroke away</h2>
    <p>
      Press <kbd>Cmd/Ctrl + K</kbd> anywhere. Type what you want – “create task”, “start timer”,
      “set alarm” – hit Enter, done. Every tool registers its actions here, so you rarely need
      the mouse.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card step">
    <h2>6 · The tools: close to 50, all local</h2>
    <p>
      Every tool ships with Cardo, runs locally and speaks to the assistant. The highlights,
      by area – the full catalog lives in <strong>⊞ Tools</strong>:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Assistant</strong> – a local AI that turns braindumps into proposal cards and can operate every tool below; optionally powered by your Claude subscription. See <a href={withBase('/assistant')}>Your Assistant</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Plan</strong> – To-Do &amp; Kanban, Eisenhower matrix, time blocking, projects &amp; milestones, goals/OKRs, calendar, daily routine.</li>
      <li><strong>Write &amp; collect</strong> – Notes (<code>.md</code> files, <code>[[wiki-links]]</code>, LaTeX), Files browser, scratchpad, sticky notes, decision log, reading list, bookmarks, code snippets.</li>
      <li><strong>Focus &amp; time</strong> – Pomodoro, workclock, alarm, countdown, clock &amp; world clock (each in several styles), soundscapes, breathing coach.</li>
      <li><strong>Health &amp; life</strong> – habits, hydration, mood journal, sleep log, workout log, meal planner, medication reminders.</li>
      <li><strong>Money</strong> – savings goals, subscriptions &amp; bills, shared expenses with settle-up, currency converter.</li>
      <li><strong>Learn &amp; utilities</strong> – Anki-class flashcards (note types &amp; cloze, FSRS or SM-2 scheduling, card browser, stats, <code>.apkg</code> import/export), statistics with heatmaps, calculator, unit converter, QR codes, password generator, random picker, colors &amp; palettes, RSS reader, weather.</li>
      <li><strong>Reference</strong> – a legal-paragraph book: save statute sections (§§ / articles) with your own comment, and fetch the official text straight from legal sources (Germany, EU, UK, Austria) with its “as of” date.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted">
      Most widgets have multiple looks: in edit mode, pick a view (e.g. matrix vs. list) right
      on the widget frame.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card step">
    <h2>6½ · Sync: your data on every device</h2>
    <p>
      Optional and <strong>off by default</strong>. In <em>Settings → Sync</em> you generate a
      key (it stays in your system keychain), enter it on your other device, pick a transport –
      your own Google Drive, any synced folder (iCloud, Dropbox, Syncthing) or a WebDAV
      server – and Cardo keeps to-dos, notes, settings and assistants in step.
      Everything is <strong>end-to-end encrypted before it leaves your device</strong>: the
      storage provider only ever sees unreadable blocks. Anyone with your key can read your
      data, so treat it like a password – and know that losing every device <em>and</em> the
      key means the synced data is gone, by design.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card step">
    <h2>7 · Make it yours: the design panel</h2>
    <p>
      In edit mode, open <strong>🎨 Design</strong>. Start with a one-click <em>design preset</em>
      (a whole look at once), then fine-tune: twenty themes from beloved community palettes
      (Catppuccin, Nord, Gruvbox, Tokyo Night, Everforest, Kanagawa …), an accent color, fonts
      and text size, a card style (soft, flat or paper), corner radius, transparency and even a
      background image. Want more? The <strong>theme editor</strong> derives your own theme from
      any palette – all 18 colors are yours to change, export and share. Your personal tweaks
      survive every theme switch, and whole boards can be exported and imported as files
      (command palette: “Export board”).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card step">
    <h2>8 · Trust, but verify: the self-test</h2>
    <p>
      <em>Settings → Diagnostics → “Run self-test”</em> checks the whole app live – database,
      every active tool, every command, themes, translations – against a scratch database
      (your real data is never touched) and gives you a report you can export. If anything ever
      feels off, run this first and share the report in the <a href={FORUM_URL} rel="noopener">forum</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card step">
    <h2>Questions?</h2>
    <p>
      The <a href={withBase('/docs')}>docs</a> answer the most common ones (where is my data?
      is it really free?). For everything else, the <a href={FORUM_URL} rel="noopener">forum</a>
      is open – no account on Cardo's side needed, just a GitHub login.
    </p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .step { margin-top: 1.25rem; }
    .step h2 { margin-top: 0; }
  </style>
</Base>
